title: Authorities say small plane has crashed near Lemoore Naval Air Station in Central California; injuries unknown - @AP
text:
Officials: Plane crashes near California military base Sep. 21, 2015 8:20 PM EDT Share article 36.7477 -119.772 
FRESNO, Calif. (AP) â€” Authorities say a plane has crashed near a military base in Central California. 
California Highway Patrol Officer Scott Jobinger says the plane went down north of the Lemoore Naval Air Station on Monday afternoon. He could not confirm if it was a military plane or if anyone was injured. 
He says the plane crashed in a dirt field about 3 miles from the end of one of the base's runways. 
Jobinger says a fire from the crash has been extinguished, and no roads have been closed. 
Lemoore Naval Air Station, about 45 miles south of Fresno, is a center for the Navy's West Coast FA-18 fighter jet operations. SEE FULL ARTICLE
